animal.description:
Marius
Breed: Catahoula Mix 
Age: 2-3 years +/- Neutered Male
Weight: 58 pounds
Dogs: Would be best as only dog
Cats: No
Kids: 12+
Crate Trained: Yes
House Trained: Yes
Location: Pennsylvania 

Hi, I'm Marius. First thing you should know is I love being outside. The entire world is fascinating, and I want to sniff every corner of it. I love hiking and going for long walks in new places. When I see something I like, I am VERY determined to get there, though I'm working on having more self-control.

At the moment, I don't mind walking on a gentle leader, only occasionally giving a tug to smell something. This skill hasn't quite transferred over to a flat collar yet. True to breed, moving objects get all of my attention when I'm outside. I am reactive to bikes, skateboards, squirrels, really any fast moving objects, and, while I'm working on it, I would need someone to help continue to show me a better way to handle myself.

Inside, I am a completely different dog. I can be relatively content laying on the couch, or at your feet, as long as you're nearby. Sometimes I'm quite snuggly, putting my head in your lap as we lay on the couch, but other times I can be aloof. Occasionally when I'm in the mood, I enjoy chasing squeaky balls around the house. I also like using my nose indoors. I play "find it" for treats, and I would enjoy doing nosework as a way to pass time. I'm pretty smart and can learn tricks quickly if you give me food that I REALLY like, however I get frustrated and bored if I'm unsure what you want me to do. I am housebroken and know my basic obedience commands (Sit, Down, Stay/"Wait", Come) however they could be proofed a bit more, as I forget some of them when I'm excited. I will sleep in my crate and consider it to be a comfy place, as long as the door is open. With a little coaxing, I'm sure I could learn to adjust to having the door closed for longer periods. The biggest thing is I need help learning that it's okay to be alone sometimes. I need someone to show me how to be calm and have fun on my own when I can't be with my human.

When it comes to others, I would probably do best as an only dog for now. I am reactive on leash to other dogs. Although I've been working on controlling my reactions, I need someone to continuously and consistently show me the best way to behave. While I haven't been tested with cats, it might be best to avoid them, as my prey drive is pretty strong. I could probably do okay with teenaged children, however small children are just too active for me. Other humans, I'm relatively neutral towards on first meeting, however when I find someone I like, I get excited to see them!

I'm looking for an experienced and dedicated owner who will help me to become the best version of myself that I can! It would be best if this person also had some land or a large yard I could burn my energy off in without being exposed to some of my triggers!

If you are interested in fostering Marius, please email sln2310@yahoo.com and request an application. Once your application has been received and reviewed, you will be contacted via email or phone by one of our volunteers.
If you are interested in adopting Marius, please email sln2310@yahoo.com and request an application. Once your application has been received and reviewed, you will be contacted via email or phone by one of our volunteers. After your application is approved, the foster parent for the dog you have selected will contact you to answer any questions you may have and determine if that dog is a good match for your family. 

If you have no particular dog in mind, we will be happy to keep your application on file and notify you if the right dog should come into rescue. Catahoula Rescue of New England is an all-volunteer group. Dogs in our program are fostered by volunteers. The foster homes care for our dogs as if they were their own. All dogs have received vaccinations appropriate to age and are spayed or neutered. 

Marius’ adoption donation is $350 which includes Rabies, DHLPP, Bordetella, fecal test, heartworm test when appropriate and is on preventative, microchip, and neuter. We do not have a physical shelter, all of our dogs are fostered in individual foster homes across the New England and Canada.
animal.name: Marius - PA

Meet Tomas, a beautiful puppy from Puerto Rico! Tomas is 1 year old and 33 pounds. He is a sweet and gentle boy who loves to cuddle and please you.

He is housebroken and knows a few commands already -he is a fast learner. He enjoys going for walks, running in the yard, and playing with his foster dog-sister. He is soft and gentle and wants to sit right on your feet! He gets nervous when he can't see his people and doesn't like to be left in a crate. Tomas is NOT suited to apartment/condo living. Tomas
is neutered, up to date on vaccinations and microchipped.

The adoption fee for this dog is $350 which includes routine vetting and spay/neuter.

***Please note that our first step is submitting an application (it does not commit you in any way but allows us to discuss with you if you and the dog are a good fit). In addition, an important step in approving adoption applicants is to complete a vet check. Vetting of current and past pets is very important to us, thus we will be speaking with the vet(s) listed on your application to ensure that your current and previous pet(s) are kept up to date on vaccines (including rabies), spayed or neutered, maintained on appropriate monthly preventatives and examined annually by your vet.***

animal.description: First, you'll be drawn in by Orion's looks. We can't resist his smokey eyeliner, auburn coat, and extra wrinkles. Once you get over how ridiculously good looking he is, you'll be wowed by his quiet, sweet demeanor. Orion knows basic commands and takes treats oh so gently from your fingers. He has very little interest in toys and prefers being right next to you and leaning in for love. He requires some time to adjust to new environments so he will need a family who will be patient with him. Orion needs continued work on his dog skills so would do best as your only dog so that he can soak up all the attention for himself. Orion completed a 6-week board and train with the Paws for Life prison program! This amazing program helps LA City homeless dogs by giving them all the basic training, socialization, and the structure they need to be successful. Orion will also be eligible for post-adoption training support through the Paws for Life program after they complete the program. You can learn more about the program here: https://pawsforlifek9.org/paws-for-life-prison-program/?fbclid=IwAR0gadA6_QY0KAN0GGAJB9kHtkZUlKjarFuj6BTikUjEjh0YliY18vE89N0If you are interested in meeting this dog, go to la.bestfriends.org/adopt, fill out our Dog Adoption Survey and our team will reach out to you!

This sweet angel is Sadie.  She is 12 years old and just so wonderful!  Sadly, Sadie has already had two homes.  Her original owner passed away and another family took her and her sister in.  After a year they decided that they couldn’t care for Sadie anymore because she is incontinent.  Sadie does have weakness in her back legs and is incontinent.  She can still walk and does go down the ramp into the yard in her foster home but she does not go up it.  Sadie loves to be with her person and will follow you all over!  If you leave the room and don’t come back in a couple minutes she gets up and comes to find you.  If she doesn’t have enough grip to stand up and walk then she will drag herself along.

Sadie is spayed, up-to-date on vaccines, heartworm negative and microchipped.  All she needs is a forever home willing to give her the love and attention that she deserves.

animal.description:
NOTE:  Due to overwhelming response for Izzy we are no longer accepting applications for her.  If you wish to fill out an application for other dogs that may come into rescue please feel free to do so.



Sweet Izzy is a four year old Frenchie mix (we do not know what she is mixed with). She is a small girl at less than 15lbs. As you can see from her picture she currently has some skin issues. Unfortunately her prior owner, who has passed away, didn't keep her on flea/tick meds and she ended up with fleas and lost all her fur as a result. We are currently working with the veterinarian on getting her all fixed up. She is on some skin meds and is getting medicated baths.

Izzy came from a home with another dog and a cat and she currently is in a foster home with several other dogs so she is fine with both. We have been working on her housebreaking and if you take her out she will go outside but if you depend on her to go out on her own she will sometimes go in the house. We are working on it and know she is catching on!

Izzy is heartworm negative and current on vaccines. She will be spayed and microchipped prior to adoption but the vet wants to wait until we work on her skin.

Although Izzy is not currently available for adoption we feel she will be very soon so please feel free to fill out an application for her at www.pawsitivelypugs.org.

My name is Harley, and I just arrived at CSAC from a shelter. My former owner wanted me to find a new home. I love people and lived with kids. I am house trained. I do not like other dogs. I had 2 doggie brothers, and we did not get along so I want to be the only king in my castle. Right now, I am in the caring hands of one of the great Vets that work with the CSAC. They are checking me out and making sure I am healthy. Hopefully, I will find my new family that will turn me into a happy, cherished pet. For more information about this dog, email our Adoption Coordinator. Our adoption process starts with an application. If you are interested in adopting this pup, please click the Adopt menu at the top of the screen, read about our process, and click the application link. We are committed to providing the best possible care for these forgotten friends. Unfortunately, the mounting high costs are beginning to limit the number of dogs we are able to take into our program. Even if you cannot adopt or foster one of our current adoptable dogs, please consider making a donation. animal.description:
Astra - Siberian Husky - Female - 2 Years - www.twyla.org

If you'd like to know more about this dog please visit our website at www.Twyla.org

Meet Astra: this GORGEOUS Siberian Husky girl has it all: she's got the looks, she's got the smarts and she has the personality - all she needs now is a home! Astra came back to us due to no fault of her own, her owner was overwhelmed and Huskies in general are a bit high maintenance, they require lots of regular exercise, a good amount of training and patience and some grooming and if not provided with that, they will find themselves in trouble. Astra is  no exception, she is smart and energetic, LOVES people and attention, and LOVES to run and play. She is quite affectionate, and gets along well with other dogs, cats are unknown. She'll probably do best with older kids as she will likely knock little kids over in her exuberance.

Astra is looking for a dog experienced home, preferably with Husky experience as she requires lots of exercise, some training, a good amount of patience and very solid fencing, as well as secure indoor containment, if left unsupervised. She will repay you with lots of snuggles and kisses and the privilege to walk around town with one of the prettiest Huskies out and about!

***Please note: All dogs are fostered in private homes of volunteers, so to meet a dog please fill out an Adoption Application on our website (http://www.twyla.org/adopt/our-adoption-process) so we may setup a private meetup with the dog or coordinate for an Introduction at the next general Adoption Meet  and Greet (as listed on our website: (http://www.twyla.org/upcoming-events), as not all dogs attend all Meet and Greets***

animal.description:
Looks like: Husky mix
Female, 13 years old, 41 pounds

Chubbs is a regal and gorgeous Husky who has fallen on hard times and is now sadly in a state of neglect. She's very emaciated and is ready for your TLC to help her gain some weight and get into better condition! 

Despite being in rough shape, she greets people with a gentle kiss and a hello. She has a gentle spirit and comfort around other dogs and with people. She walks nicely on leash but does get eager to meet other dogs, pulling with a desire to sniff. Chubbs is good with children and is happy to receive pets from them. After a safe and proper introduction, Chubbs is sharing space and is very respectful toward the cat in her foster home. If Chubbs sees a cat outside or on a walk, she will want to lunge and vocally inform you that there is one there. 

When she hears sirens on the tv she will do a cute Husky howl. She likes to have her head out the window in the car. She does follow her people around as she just wants to be included. She will come up and put her head in your lap when she wants cuddles and pets. She loves to be included on the couch or to hang by your chair to receive as much love as you can give. 

Chubbs has a sweet disposition and she'd appreciate being in a home with another dog because it will make her feel more at home. She'd also do well in a home where she can get tons of attention. A mellow home is best, where she gets walks but will having plenty of nap time while her person works. 

Chubbs was seized from a bad living situation by Hitchcock Road Animal Services. They asked POMDR to take her and help her find the life she deserves.

animal.description:
Hello all!  Did I just melt your heart?  I knew I would!  My name is Lola and I am 15 years old.  I was happy in my home with my mom and then the unthinkable happened, she passed away due to something called covid.  I don’t know what that is.  All I know is that my world was turned upside down!  I went to live with a lady that was a coworker of my moms and she kept me for a couple weeks while working to get me into rescue.  She really liked me and wanted to keep me but she lived in an apartment and she was already at their pet limit so she couldn’t.

A little about myself.  Like I said, I am 15 years old.  When I got to rescue they checked me over and said that I needed a dental.  I had bloodwork and the vet said I was good to go to have my teeth cleaned.  I came home from my dental with just 3 teeth!!  Yup, I had a mouth full of rotten teeth but it has all been taken care of and my lack of teeth has not stopped me from eating dry kibble (though I would love canned ?).  I cannot actually hear you but I can see just a little, maybe a foot, so I get around well.  I am currently in a foster home with other dogs and I am ok with that.  I just tell them what I think when they bump into me!  Yes, I can be feisty!

What am I looking for in a forever home?  My requests aren’t much.  I would love a home where I am an only dog or one that I am one of only two or three dogs.  I am old and I like to chill and relax without others bothering me.  If you would give me a comfortable bed in a quiet place that would be my dream!  See, not a lot, just a quiet house and a comfy bed!

Do you think you can give me a wonderful home to spend my golden years?  If so, please fill out an application at www.pawsitivelypugs.org and ask for me!

animal.description:
Senior Hearts Rescue and Renewal is the only licensed senior dog rescue organization in Western Pennsylvania. We do not have a shelter or a public facility. ALL of our dogs reside in foster homes in the greater Pittsburgh, PA area. 

We are a 100% volunteer organization. Please respect our volunteers' time. If a dog is listed on PetFinder, he/she IS available for adoption. We cannot reply to messages, phone calls, and emails about a dog until we have received, reviewed, and approved an adoption application. 

Our ADOPTION application is found at www.seniorhearts.org Completing this application is the first step in our adoption screening process. You MUST complete the application in its entirety in order to be considered as a potential adopter.  Please select "More About Us" for further details on our adoption requirements.  You can meet a dog ONLY after we have completed our adoption approval process.

If you are looking at the dog below, it most certainly means the dog is available for adoption. We look forward to receiving your application in hopes that you are able to meet our adoption requirements and provide this dog with a loving furever home.

A message from Flash...

My name is Flash and I am an 11-year young big boy weighing in at 70 pounds.  Can you imagine?  70 pounds of all love!  I am blind in one eye and can't see very well out of the other one, but that doesn't stop me from my walks and greeting everyone I walk by.  I am super friendly and love all animals and humans I encounter. I would love a sibling but it's not a deal-breaker.  

My ideal home would be ranch style living. I can’t really do steps.  I prefer a calm adult only home environment. After all, I am an elderly guy. 

If you are looking for a snug bug best friend who is happy all the time, I am your guy.  I promise all the unconditional love you want. I can be adopted within a two-hour radius of Pittsburgh, PA. If you are interested in giving me a furever home, you must first complete the adoption application at www.seniorhearts.org

animal.description:
We are so pleased to finally introduce you to an exceptionally special girl named NIYA! This 2 yr-old, 38lb, mystery of a mixed breed has the sweetest one-of-a-kind personality and is seeking the pawfect owner to help nurture her brave, confident and best self! 

BACKGROUND:
This cutie has come so FAR from when we first rescued her! Saved from an awful animal hoarding situation, “skinny girl” as she was called had spent most of her life locked up in a bedroom with no socialization or training! Incredibly scared and frightened (and very pregnant!), Niya was moved to an amazing foster home! 

Within a month, this sweet girl gave birth to 10 beautiful puppies! Although this was a scary experience for Niya (who ran away from the first few pups!), she received excellent guidance from her foster mom and turned into the most amazing mama dog!  

PERSONALITY:
Niya is a sweetheart, but can get nervous around new people and scare easily out of her comfort zone. She has NEVER been aggressive (is the happiest dog in her foster home!) and is extremely fond of dogs and toys! We’re not sure about cats as she loves to chase little furry things (and may need some guidance meeting a cat!). She’s a complete snuggle bug and likes to sneak into her foster’s bed occasionally, but prefers her spot on the couch! She enjoys watching TV, especially if there’s animal and will sometimes try to find the featured dog or cat behind the TV! She may bark at her reflection and likes to nudge you with her nose or paw to be petted if you aren’t giving her enough attention! 

BEHAVIOR:
Niya LOVES other dogs and is feeling more and more confident about humans! She has also learned to like children, but may do better in a home with older children (or children who have been taught how to respect their pets). She is completely house-trained + crate-trained, knows how to use the doggy door like a PRO and loves to feel LOVED and give out just as much LOVE!  

The PAWFECT owner:
1) Niya would greatly benefit from an owner who had the patience to continue her healing journey. This someone would help ease her into new surroundings, learn how to be exposed to new experiences in baby steps and how to feel confident in the outside world (and earn back those years inside that single bedroom!). 

2) Niya loves to please and has a willingness to learn – however – she isn’t fond of the leash! We are not sure if this is due to past experiences, but she becomes quite scared at seeing it. Additional training to associate the leash with something “positive” may need to be administered! (tips- high value treats + gradual conditioning)

3) The ideal house would need a fenced-in-yard.

4) Niya is spayed, up-to-date on shots and microchipped!

If you’d like more information or are interested in this precious girl, please text 4-6 photo's of your interior/exterior home and yard (including fence if applicable) to Heather at 770-714-4352.

- - -

Please Note: Inquiries through Pet Finder may be slower to respond and the best form of communication/inquiry would be through text message at the number above. Thank you.

Search for "A PAW AND A PRAYER DOG RESCUE" on Facebook to see ALL our available dogs for adoption updated daily!

animal.description:
**Justice will be available for adoption approximately Feb 1st following heartworm treatment**
Hi I'm Justice. I'm a good boy who enjoys hanging out next to my people. BIG comfy dog beds are my favorite! I also enjoy  going on long walks and exploring all the different sights and smells. I'm good on a leash and will go wherever you want us to go. I’m fully potty trained and will stand by the door to let you know when I need to go out. I love cuddling up on the couch but just so you know I’m a total couch hog. I like everyone but kids over 10 would be best for me, my tail is pretty lethal as I just get so happy around everyone. I don't jump and I love to give kisses and get lots of scratches. I'm just a big ole love bug! I smile at everyone I meet. I would love to meet you. 

Justice came from rural southern Oklahoma where he was found as a stray and never reclaimed. The only way he would make it out of the shelter alive was to be rescued as they do not have any volunteer or adoption programs in their rural animal control facility. Dolly's Legacy came to his rescue and saved his life. Justice is a male Yellow Lab who weighs 70 lbs and was born approximately 11-1-17. He is neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, given flea/tick preventative, dewormed. Justice had life-saving treatment for heartworm disease. He will need to remain on heartworm preventative for life, as is recommended for ALL dogs, and retested in 6 months to ensure he is heartworm free. Adoption fee is $450 to help offset the many expenses we have for vetting costs. We rely strictly on adoption fees and donations to continue to save the lives of orphaned & abandoned pets; 100% goes towards their care. If interested in adopting one of our available dogs or puppies, please complete an online adoption application at https://dollyslegacyanimalrescue.org/adopt/ You will be contacted by our adoption coordinator via email after your application has been reviewed & approved to schedule an appointment.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Meet Joey! He's so gorgeous! He's the full Pyr package - a big ol' white lovable giant. Born around December 2016, he is a healthy 90 pounds.

Joey is so charming! He is sweet, friendly, playful, goofy, and a huge fluffball! Not to mention he is smart and a fast learner.

Even after being found as a stray, Joey has always shown himself to be a happy, loving boy. He loves all people and happily will receive hugs from everyone. He loves getting scratches, playing with toys, running in the yard, and playing catch, but (true to his Pyr heritage) he doesn't always bring the ball back! Joey is still learning that not everything is a toy, but he is eager to please and is quickly learning.

His fondest wish is for a human to be home most of the time. He loves companionship, and will follow you around the house and often takes his nap at your feet.

He can be too big and playful for young children. If there are kids in his forever home, they need to be older and big enough that they won't get knocked down by him.

Joey will try singing with you sometimes by howling or mumbling along and has been known to talk back to you when he's super excited. He will bark at suspicious noises and squirrels in the backyard, but he isn't on guard while inside and is quiet.

Joey would be happiest in a home with another big doggie playmate. He loves playing with dogs, following them around, sleeping next to them, cuddling with them, and being in close contact.

He has also been cat tested and did well.

He is leash trained, and he loves going on daily walks! He relishes meeting new people and new dogs and greeting them all! He loves to smell everything, so often needs coaxing to keep moving his booty forward!

Joey is house trained and crate trained. He sits at the back door to let you know he needs to go outside to potty.

He has been fine with the 4' fence at his foster home. Sometimes he needs encouragement to come inside at night from his dirt bed.

He rides contentedly in a car; occasionally he needs a little sweet-talk before he'll get into it.

This beautiful boy will delight his forever family!

SPIN Pyrs are all in foster homes in the Dallas/Fort Worth area. Potential adopters are asked to make travel arrangements if they live elsewhere. All SPIN dogs are spayed or neutered, current on vaccinations and on heartworm prevention. Please go to our website www.SpinRescue.org and fill out an application for this great Great Pyrenees!

animal.description:
Looks like: Chihuahua/Terrier
Male, 8 years old, 10 pounds

Chewy is a shy guy that desperately wants to be loved, but on his terms. He came to us from the SPCA for Monterey County because the shelter environment was just too loud for this little fella to thrive. He is good with other dogs, rides nicely in the car and has an adorable little face! 

Chewy is still really uncertain in new situations and can be fussy about being handled, so we think a quiet, patient, adult-only home would be best for him. If you have other accepting dogs to show him the ropes, that would probably suit him well. He can nap around and share space with other dogs. He is not experienced with walking on leash and mostly tags along next to the person but if he feels the pull, he rebels and fights it with an opposite pull and a little tantrum. 

If lefty in the home alone he does ok if distracted with a treat but is sure excited for his person to return. He wants to follow his people around the home and sometimes shows off his play for a few minutes with a toy. at night, he can sleep in a crate but will send a whimper of protest at first. He really desires a lap in the car and will act like he cannot ride comfortably and safely without a lap. This guy really does love to be held as much as possible, and that includes being snuggles. He will give kisses in return. He definitely wants to be a good dog and give love to his person. He has a cute personality that really shines once he is comfortable. His ideal home has a patient person and a consistent routine that will lead to Chewy's settling and feeling comfortable. 

Chewy is not a fan of the leash yet. He may cower from it pulling him and he needs to build confidence with a person and then be shown how to be lead with leash, perhaps with a tasty treat. Thankfully, this guy will crawl right into your lap or arms and is very content being carried.

animal.description:
Hi there! I'm Polly and I'm a ~5 year old, 60lbs Pit Bull terrier mix. I was just recently rescued from the HIT living team, and I am still coming out of my shell, and allowing myself to be loved... I have never experienced that before, and it feels soooo good :) 

- I am a SUPER sweet and observant girl, and just a big bundle of LOVE. 

- I am timid but gaining confidence quickly and am a fast learner, especially when there are other dogs around me who can show me the ropes!

- I am not super treat or food motivated, although I LOVE deli meat, and really like a nice bone to chew on :) 
 
- My favorite things to do is lounging around on the sofa or dog bed for most of the day, with my human by my side. I am a big sweet couch potato. 
 
- I was timid on walks and in new places at first, but I have already learned to gain so much more confidence in such little time, and I'm loving the new me! 

- I have never really been in a home before my foster home, so I am still learning house rules and boundaries like what I can sit and jump on, but I am very responsive to a stern "no" from my owner if I'm doing something that is not allowed, like putting my paws on the counter. I haven't had any accidents in the home though, so I am potty trained! 
 
- I LOVE other dogs, and absolutely would love a home with other dog friends who could boost my confidence and show me how to be a doggo, but also not a necessity. 
 
- My ideal home setting is in a home with a gentle and sweet individual or family, who will have the patience to teach me all the joys of being a dog, and lots and lots of love and cuddles!!!!!!

If you see me online I am still available for adoption! If you are interested in adopting me please fill out an application here: www.hitlivingfoundation.org/adoption-application, and email a video walkthrough of your home and yard to BOTH Nicole@hitlivingfoundation.org AND Marta@hitlivingfoundation.org. Your application will not be counted as valid without your video. You will hear back from us within a few days.

animal.description:
Orry-O is a male, 33 lb., black and white Rat Terrier mix. Orry-O's estimated date of birth is December, 2014. Poor Orry-O is a victim of a really bad situation and he needed help! He has a teenage brother that didn’t know how to treat him with respect and love and his mother had to save him from that hurt. She did not want to let him go and it is obvious he was well-loved. He does have some missing fur from flea dermatitis, but should be better from that soon. He is settling in and would be a great laid back dog for someone that wants a calm, established dog in their life! Orry-O has a $150.00 adoption fee plus the cost of 6 months of heartworm prevention. 

Note: ARF reserves the right to deny any application that is deemed unsuitable for the animal. Please be aware that our animal adoptions are NOT on a first come- first serve basis. Our sole purpose is to find the best possible home for the animals that fall under our care. We do not ship our animals. All adopters are expected to come to Tulsa if approved.

For details on how to adopt please visit http://www.arftulsa.org/adopt.

animal.description:
HI!  I am Ben.  But I respond better to Puppy.
     I am a very shy, super sweet, loving cuddly little guy with huge ears.  I am mostly quiet but can bark loud if I decide too.
I am great with kids and currently have a 2 yr girl I love to play and take nappy naps with.
     I have a lot of doggy buddies in my foster home and mostly we play great together.  I am leery because I got torn up pretty good by a very big dog before I was rescued and treated.  
     I am house trained and use the 24 hr open dog door on my own.  I don't seem to know any commands but am very well behaved and great on a leash.  I love to travel in the car.  I usually sleep with my foster mama but also like my fav dog bed and blanket, too. 
     In my foster home, I am never alone so my mom can't know how I behave when solo for any period of time.  I have never done anything my mom has had to correct me for yet.
     I am an amazing little sweetheart and will make a great addition to a calm,  loving new home.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Marshall County Humane Society is now following CDC guidelines for Covid-19 in order to keep everyone as safe as possible. We are showing dogs and cats to prospective adopters, but only on the grounds outside our shelter. We will need appointment to show the animal and we will want to have social distancing of 6' while you are there and we are wearing masks. We are doing Zoom interviews to see inside of your home since we aren't going into homes for home visit. We do come to your home before finalizing adoption to check the security of your fence if you are adopting a dog. Our dogs are given much care and attention and we treat every medical need of animal once we take them in.
MCHS is a limited intake adoption center. We are an all volunteer, non-profit organization. All of our animals are disease free, have been spayed/neutered and are up to date on shots. We charge a Dog adoption fee of $125 which includes a microchip. Our Cat adoption fee is $75.00. Most of our dogs will require a fenced yard. To fill out application, go to our website Marshallcountyhumanesociety.org, go to Adoption Info tab and click on Application. For more info, call 662-564-2900. The girls tell me they like the white motley throat marking I have. I really want a home so I promise I'll work hard to be a good boy if you take me home. I try to be cooperative with the other dogs at the shelter so would probably get along with your other dogs or cats too. . The vet says I probably was born in December, 2018 so I can probably listen to your instructions pretty well. Call to see me soon by calling 662-564-2900 or E-mail DogsNCats11@gmail.com to make an appointment to meet me. I will need a fenced yard.
All our animals have been spayed or neutered and up to date on all preventives and shots and we are microchipped. Dog adoption fee is $125.
Fill out application at Marshallcountyhumanesociety.org and go to Adoption Info Tab.

animal.description:
Oreo was rescued from Puerto Rico as a puppy and was adopted very quickly. However, he recently was returned to Eleventh Hour Rescue as he was just a little too high energy for his adopter's life style. Oreo would love a fenced in backyard to burn his energy off, and a lot of exercise throughout the day. This is not a dog that can be crated for long hours at a time.

Oreo is now about a year old & weighs 45 pounds. He has the most striking blue eyes which give him a unique look. He's a happy guy who loves belly rubs, car rides & playing fetch!

Oreo hasn't had much socialization with other dogs, and after dog testing him we know that he should be the only dog in the home. He can see other dogs socially, but sharing his space is another matter. He does wonderful on pack walks, just doesn't like other dogs in his face. He is a friendly boy who is good with people who can give him his space but would be best in an adult only home due to his exuberance . Oreo can be protective of his toys and treats, so he needs an owner with experience who will know when to leave him alone. He's a beautiful boy who deserves to be in a home!

If you've got a place in your heart and your home for this blue-eyed boy, please fill out an adoption application at www.ehrdogs.org & be sure to mention his name!

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Kitten is a sweet girl she loves to get lots of love. She is shy at first but once she warms up she will love you. Kitten is very selective on the dogs she does like. Kitten was found as a stray trapped inside the fencing of a retention pond. She is a sweet dog,who gravitates towards women, slowly warms up to men. A quiet home with owners who will maintain balance and give her lots of love. She is picky about her canine friends here at the center, so we think she'd prefer to be the only dog in the home. A FENCED YARD FOR HER TO SAFELY PLAY AND ROMP IS RECOMMENDED.

DOG 4 A DAY UPDATE:
We took Kitten out twice and can tell potential adopters that she will make a great additional to any family. She is easy to walk, house trained and was so calm during car rides. We took her to the waterfront for al long walk and to relax at our home. At home she was very gentle and curious about everything but only played with dog toys. She does jump when she hears loud noises, like the garage door, but I think with time she will get use to all the usual noises in a home.

animal.description:
Our gorgeous girl Kitsu is looking for an experienced family to be her furever home. Kitsu (who also answers to Kit, and Kitsa), is a wonderfully smart, independent girl who will brighten your day with her vibrant energy. She knows a number of basic cues, has lovely leash manners, and even hides a few other tricks up her sleeves :) Kitsu is incredibly food motivated - seriously, she is able to sniff out a crumb from two rooms away. This smart girl will benefit with adequate amounts of mental stimulation to channel her energy in positive and constructive manners. Since coming into rescue, Kitsu has shown to be an extremely playful girl, almost as if she is making up for lost time. She adores attention, but only after she deems you worthy of her affection, so you have to be patient in order to earn her trust. Once she decides to accept you into her inner circle, she will not hesitate to tell you all the details about her day, and we do mean, EVERY SINGLE DETAIL :) She would be great as your one and only dog as she can be picky about other canines. This beautiful girl will need an experienced handler familiar with the breed who has the time and patience to work with her, and help her get settled into her new home. Kitsu will benefit from consistent positive reinforcement training, and amateur dog sports may be a productive way to challenge her brilliant mind. This girl is ready for the next chapter of her life. Are you ready to give her a chance to love you and be your furever companion?

NYS Registered Rescue # RR102
View full listing, fee and online application at - www.nationalpyr.org/adoptable-dogs (sorry, no phone submissions, but if you would like more information you can email us at renpyrgroup@yahoo.com).

Secure VISIBLE fencing is required; invisible fencing WILL NOT contain this breed. 

Our goal is to assess every application on its own merits. Key considerations are: 1) the experience of the applicant with large breed dogs 2) children in the household or regularly visiting the household are ready for a large-breed dog who is a guardian by nature (www.nationalpyr.org/know-the-breed) and 3) the sex of other dogs currently residing in the household to avoid same-sex aggression issues. For puppies under six months old, the applicant’s ability to socialize the puppy with older dogs is a priority.

animal.description:
If you are looking for an independent, mature girl to join your pack, Izzy may be the pyrfect girl for you! In her previous life, Izzy has been left outdoors in sun and rain, regardless of the weather, and she always had to fend for herself, sometimes even having to scavenge for food. Since coming into rescue, Izzy is slowly learning that a home provides not only a place of shelter, but also food, love and affection. Despite having been neglected most of her life, Izzy is not hesitant to approach people and is more than happy to show her affection. You can easily win her over with a good head scratch and nice belly rub :) Given her history, Izzy would prefer to have a large, fenced-in backyard where she can safely patrol and guard the property. As she is in her golden years, she will need a little more attention taking care of her arthritis; she is not going to let stiff joints stop her from doing her job, so it will be important for her humans to look out for her to keep her healthy for as long as possible. This sweet girl will need some help settling into a new routine in her new home, but she is quite food motivated so that it 'is' possible to teach an old dog new tricks! Will you open your home and show Izzy the love and affection that she so deserves?

NYS Registered Rescue # RR102

animal.description:
Yinzer is a Boxer/American Bulldog mix who is almost 8 years old. His birthday is January 25th, 2013. He was adopted by his original owner at 6 weeks old. He is a very loyal and loving dog. Since then, the owner and their family has grown with the addition of two children, 3 years old and 7 months old. 

Yinzer needs an owner that is good with dogs and able to show leadership with confident verbal commands. He listens well and follows verbal commands once you earn his trust. 

He can feel the emotions of people who are scared and worried which makes him alarmed and protective that something bad may happen. It will take some time for a new owner to establish a relationship with him but he without a doubt will make someone very happy and will become very attached to them. 

Yinzer does best with meeting new people in a common area that is not his. This way he does not feel like he needs to protect his space or loved ones from a threat. When living with his previous owners he would invite new people into the house by meeting them in the driveway first. Once he was able to meet a new person in a common area outside of the yard and house such as the driveway, he would be welcoming to that guest. Once that person has been welcomed into the home, that person would be able to return time after time without needing to meet Yinzer anymore in the driveway.

Over time Yinzer did develop a protective nature of his owner and the family. So much that when the owners 3-year-old daughter tried to surprise tickle attack the owner, she did it inches in front of Yinzers face and he unfortunately bit her not realizing it was her. 

In the days following the incident Yinzer was around the family and daughter prior to being surrendered and he showed sadness, remorse and no aggression. However, the owner feels it to be the best option to find him a loving home with no small children and a simpler household. 

Yinzer is an amazing dog who will make someone very happy. He enjoys taking walks and laying around a fenced in yard. 

He does well with other dogs that like to play. He would not do well with an Alpha Male who was already living in the house. But he did do well when the original owner introduced a female beagle into the family 5 years ago. They would play, wrestle and sleep next to each other every day. He also does will with other dogs of friends of the owner that would come and visit. 

Like with most dogs, toys are usually removed when friends dogs would visit. But the dogs would wrestle and play for hours without an issue. 

Yinzer is house trained and can be left in a house for up to 10 hours if needed. 
He sleeps well in the bedroom or a different room. He is not a dog that will do well sleeping outside or being left outside for long periods of time. 

He is a very low maintenance, cuddle friendly lap dog who is in a larger dog’s body. Be ready for his heavy head to lay on your lap while watching tv with your new best friend.

He is scared because of the dramatic changes over the past few weeks and will need a little time to understand that he is safe in a new home with you. 

Interested in adopting? Go on our website, triadspca.org and submit an application or call us at 336-375-3222.

animal.description:
Hi I’m Lucille! I am a pure bred Great Pyrenees somewhere between 5 and 7 years old. 
I love to be petted and want to be around you always! I’m a little slow due to my age and hip dysplasia. (Which I take some joint and pain medication for). But I still love walks! 
I enjoy being with other dogs most definitely. I am not sure about cats as I haven’t been around any.  I have tested positive for heartworm but I am taking daily medications to get me all better.  
I have a hearty appetite - more food more happy! I’m not spayed yet and I am working on my house training which is getting better every day. 
My life hasn’t been an easy one, it’s likely someone was using me for breeding and then dumped me when I wasn’t useful anymore. But despite this ugly past, I am an absolute sweetheart with so much love to give. I’m looking to give lots of love and share a happy life with a special someone.

If you are interested in meeting and/or adopting, the first step is to please visit our website to complete an application and read all of our FAQs: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/adopt 

**An inquiry/question on Petfinder is NOT an application. All known details about our animals are posted on their profile and updated daily. Other info would be discussed in detail with the foster during the application review process. Due to the number of inquires received (hundreds daily) we ask you submit an application on our website (that application can be used for any dog with Take Paws Rescue).

 The adoption fee for adult dogs covers age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, spay/neuter if not yet performed, heartworm test & appropriate heartworm treatment by the rescue's vet. All dogs in our care are also kept up-to-date on HW/Flea Prevention. Please see our website for more information.

*Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our puppies live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. An application will be required to make sure it’s the perfect match!

For additional information, including the adoption process and our adoption fee scale for all our adoptable pets, see our FAQs page: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/faq

animal.description:
PAWLEE

Pawlee is a 7 month old Shepherd mix.  She is great with other dogs and loves people.  Pawlee walks good on a leash, but be prepared because she likes to hold the leash and walk herself.  She is crate trained and would benefit from a basic training class.

No small children, as she still hasn't mastered the art of keeping all four paws on the ground.

She will be available after Jan 10th.

Filling out an application is the first step in the adoption process. If you have questions, the best way to contact us is to email azdesertrottis@aol.com.

We don't always bring all animals to our adoption events so check ahead of time to make sure the animal you are interested in is still available. Some animals listed may already be promised.

Arizona Desert Rotti & Pals Rescue is a NO KILL rescue serving Tucson and the surrounding area. 

We do adopt out of area under the right circumstances. If you are willing to travel to Tucson to meet us, and to personally transport your adopted pet home, we may be willing to work with you. 

A home visit is usually required for the safety of our animals. We check the yard to make sure this little pup cannot escape, no predator can get in, and also look for hazardous plants. 

We do not adopt our dogs out unless you have a secured, fenced yard, it’s a requirement for the safety of the dog. At the end of the application, please include the type of fencing and the height of the fence you have around your yard. 

If you're interested in Pawlee or any of our dogs, please fill out a pre application at: http://www.azdesertrotti.com/html/to_adopt.htm
Once you have filled out the pre-adoption application, someone will contact you about the dog to answer your questions and tell you where our Sunday adoption event is held.

Our dogs are bathed, dewormed, vet checked, given their required shots, spayed or neutered, and microchipped. 

Our rescues are homed with foster parents. They are fostered in homes so that we can tell you a little bit about their personalities, feeding schedule, habits, behavior, whether they get along with other dogs. We can tell you if they are crate trained, if they are leash trained and house trained. Most dogs need a refresher course on potty training when they go to a new home. They need to learn your routine, and it will be up to you to teach them. 

Even the most abused animals can be wonderful pets. It takes patience, love and good food, along with fun and commitment to the animal. Fosters work with these animals. They are a part of our families, while we are lucky enough to have them.

Hayward

Located in Western NE/ Northern CO/Eastern WY

 Anatolian Shepherd mix 

1-2 years old

Good with dogs

Cats unknown 

Good with the kids he's interacted with at the shelter 

Potentionally house trained but hard to tell in the shelter

Not sure on crate training or commands but he is incredibly easily motivated and very sweet

Fully vetted beyond being neutered which will happen in the next few weeks 

63lbs

 

This large lug found himself as a stray right before Christmas. No home, no family, no cozy moments by the fire for Hayward. Hayward's Christmas wish this year is just to LIVE. He's a fantastic dog, easy going, he's been a good boy! He doesn't know why he's stuck in this scary place. He just wants to focus on loving his people and being loved in return, and yes maybe he's hoping to having a place that Santa can find him in 2 days! 

 

 $200.00 Adoption Fee 

(Which is considered a non refundable donation and being we are a 501c3 organization it is tax deductible. The fee itself is not negotiable, our vets don't negotiate and thus neither do we.)

To Contact Us

Fill out our Foster Application at https://www.highplainspaw.org/foster-application

Email us at highplainspaw@gmail.com

Call our voicemail at (402)957-1578

WE DO NOT HAVE A FACILITY ALL OUR DOGS ARE LOCATED IN FOSTER HOMES. This means there is no place for you to go in person to view our dogs. We ask that an application be filled out and we will go from there!

animal.description:
If you have ANY QUESTIONS or are truly interested in adopting any animal from PAW Animal Shelter Please, fillout an adoption application FIRST! WE are a high intake No Kill Shelter ran by a staff of 4 and do not always have time to answer every question asked by so many. If you are a good fit for the animal you are interested in -we will call to speak with you, If we feel you are not a good fit , we will contact you about other pets that may be a good fit for your home. Many people are losing the opportunity to adopt the animal they want because they fail to put in an application and the pet was adopted before we could answer your email. .If you have applied for an animal in our facility and have not received a response within 7 days, PLEASE call or contact us again. Though we do our best in trying to answer all emails in a timely manner, sometimes things get away from us, get lost or misplaced. It is never our intention to ignore a request about an adoptable animal in our facility.

Sandy Brown, Director, PAW Animal Shelter

animal.description:
Mayze is hoping to get a head start to the new year with a family of her own that she can love and cuddle with. This little girl was found as a stray, and is as sweet as can be! Since coming into rescue, she has thoroughly enjoyed the company of her foster siblings...in fact, she would not let any of them out of her sight :) Not only does Mayze love playing with her foster siblings, she is also quick to catch on to the basic cues that they have already mastered, and we think she may out-perform them in no time! Mayze adores toys of all varieties. If there is a stray toy somewhere, Mayze will be sure to "rescue" it and add to her ever-growing collection of toys. This funny girl seems to particularly like soft towels or blankets - if there is one left on the floor unattended, she will most likely relocate it somewhere to nest on. Mayze is a lovely girl who will thrive in a loving family who will help her boost her confidence in navigating this busy world full of people. With a little patience and consistent training, we have no doubt that this girl will mature into a loving, loyal companion!

NYS Registered Rescue # RR102
View full listing, fee and online application at - www.nationalpyr.org/adoptable-dogs (sorry, no phone submissions, but if you would like more information you can email us at renpyrgroup@yahoo.com).

Secure VISIBLE fencing is required; invisible fencing WILL NOT contain this breed.

Our goal is to assess every application on its own merits. Key considerations are: 1) the experience of the applicant with large breed dogs 2) children in the household or regularly visiting the household are ready for a large-breed dog who is a guardian by nature (www.nationalpyr.org/know-the-breed) and 3) the sex of other dogs currently residing in the household to avoid same-sex aggression issues. For puppies under six months old, the applicant’s ability to socialize the puppy with older dogs is a priority.

Prior to being rescued, many of our dogs have experienced minimal socialization. As a result, there is often an adjustment period when learning about life as a family pet. We typically do not adopt dogs to homes with young children. Homes with older children will be considered on an individual basis. Common skills such as house training and leash walking will often take a little extra time. Patience, understanding and a gentle hand are a must. The great news is, most of these dogs come around rather quickly and being a part of their rehabilitation is an extremely rewarding experience. animal.description: **AVAILABLE FOR ADOPTION approximately 3-1-21 following heartworm treatment**  Hey y’all! My name is Ruby and I’m a cute little gal from Oklahoma. Not too long ago I found myself at a rural pound with my time almost up. I could not believe my luck when I was chosen for rescue by Dolly’s Legacy! Now that I’m safe and secure my favorite things are food, affection, and sleeping with my head under a pillow. Can you just stay home and pet me all day? My big brown eyes and soft thick fur make this a pretty appealing offer, I can assure you. I will even climb onto your lap if you let me! I’m not a very shy girl but am a bit nervous. However I’m also very smart and attentive, so a little training goes a long way in helping me settle into new situations and build confidence. I’m getting more comfortable in my foster home and every day show I am a little more confident. I used to watch the other dogs play or wait until they were done with their toys before I took a turn, but now I like to join right in on the fun. I know some basic commands and love to show them off, and when given treats I take them very gently. I have a medium amount of energy right now, but that may change once I’m feeling better after my heartworm treatment is finished. I probably had a litter of puppies at some point in my life since I was only recently spayed and I love to groom the foster puppy that lives with me. Since I'm a Heeler, I would do best with a home with kids over 10 or no kids, I would probably want to herd them. I do show some herding behavior, but mostly I’ll just herd you to the couch so you’ll sit down and pet me. Sometimes my instincts kick in towards smaller dogs, but I play really well with dogs my size or larger. I am friendly and accepting when meeting new dogs, but if they give me attitude I have no problem sticking up for myself! I would probably do best with other dogs who are calm and submissive (but still playful), but I’m willing to meet anyone to see if it’s a good fit. I’ve already done most of the hard work for you since I am house trained and kennel trained, and if you have a dog door with a fenced in yard I’ll even take myself out every time I need to. Now all I need is to find a family who will continue building my confidence through basic obedience, leash training, and positive new experiences. I have so much love to give and I can’t wait to find my forever home!   Ruby is a female Red Heeler who weighs 30 lbs and was born approximately 12-12-18. She is spayed, vaccinated, microchipped, given flea/tick preventative, dewormed. Ruby is undergoing life-saving treatment for heartworm disease. She will need to remain on heartworm preventative for life, as is recommended for ALL dogs, and retested in 6 months to ensure she is heartworm free. Adoption fee is $400 to help offset the many expenses we have for vetting costs. We rely strictly on adoption fees and donations to continue to save the lives of orphaned & abandoned pets; 100% goes towards their care. If interested in adopting one of our available dogs or puppies, please complete an online adoption application at https://dollyslegacyanimalrescue.org/adopt/ You will be contacted by our adoption coordinator via email after your application has been reviewed & approved to schedule an appointment.

animal.description:
Sasha is a 2-year-old mixed breed rescued from a high-kill shelter. This dog is current on vaccinations, microchipped, 4dx/heartworm tested, and spayed. This dog is also tested with other dogs, kennel-trained, and housebroken. We would love for you to meet this dog and see if it might be a good fit for your home. 

The first step to adoption is completing an adoption application on our website at www.bounceanimalrescue.org. Pending approval, your application is valid for 1 year, and you will be eligible to request a hold on an individual animal. The hold does not require that you adopt the animal, but ensures you get to meet and make an adoption decision prior to other applicants. Hold times cannot exceed 5 days. Also pending approval, you will be able to acquire foster home contact information, so you inquire on personalities of specific animals.

***COVID-19 Update: While we typically host weekly Saturday adoption events, in order to follow the CDC's recommendation for COVID-19 protocols, we will be suspending our weekly Saturday adoption events until given the clear. Adoptions for individual animals will occur by private adoption appointment and/or adoption handoff. Appointments and handoffs are scheduled pending staff, foster home, and vetting schedules. Because we are 100% foster-based, adoption appointments and handoffs are only offered for individual animals. When adopting at an appointment, please be aware that you will be taking the animal home that day. We can not hold animals to be picked up at a later date.

Due to CDC's recommended COVID-19 protocols, we are highly encouraging foster homes and adopters to speak with one another via phone or video chat to ensure compatible matches and limit in-person contact. If meeting in person, our foster homes are encouraged to wear masks, socially distance, and choose an outdoor meeting spot. Should you want to proceed forward with the adoption, all adoption paperwork, medical records, and adoption fees are to be completed electronically. Quick and low-contact animal handoff is also being encouraged amongst foster homes and adopters. As always, we include a one-week trial period with all our adoptions. ***

Please note, we do not have the ability to process adoption applications at our adoption events, so please plan accordingly. If an application is submitted past 5pm on Monday-Thursday, it will begin review the following day. If submitted on Friday-Sunday, it will begin review on Monday. It takes approximately 48-72 hours for an application to be processed.

For additional questions regarding meeting this dog please contact us via text/email at 970.699.6772, or contact@bounceanimalrescue.org. We apologize for any inconvenience, but due to a high volume of inquiries, calls and voicemails regarding adoption will not be returned.

Thank you for choosing adoption! If you would like more information on our organization please visit our website at www.bounceanimalrescue.org.

animal.description:
Dawson is a happy little bundle of energy. It's rare that you will see him without a toy in his mouth and even more rare that you will see him not wagging his tail. Shelter life hasn't gotten this boy down (yet)! While we haven't been able to fully dog test him - he did have one buddy here that he would happily run around the yard with. Dawson seems to enjoy the company of other dogs, but probably doesn't want a dog that will be jumping all over him. Dawson is looking for a person or family who will run around with him, play tug-of-war & fetch, and then cuddle up to you for belly rubs. One of Dawson's favorite things is going for a ride in the car! He gets sooo relaxed and pretty soon after you'll probably be hearing some soft snores. He loves everyone he meets and wiggles his whole body in excitement when he sees you (usually with a toy in his mouth). We think our sweet Dawson would do best with kids 6 years and older since he's so wiggly he could accidentally knock a small child over (and watch out for that wagging tail)! Dawson is the sweetest boy with SO much love to give a lucky person or family.

APPROXIMATE WEIGHT: 45 - POUNDS

ESTIMATED DOB: 10/11/2018

GOOD WITH OTHER DOGS: SELECTIVE

GOOD WITH KIDS: YES 6 &^ DUE TO HAPPY TAIL!

GOOD WITH CATS: NO

REQUIRES A FENCE: NO

ACTIVITY LEVEL: MODERATE

LIKES TO VOCALIZE: SOME

SPECIAL NEEDS: NONE

BREED EXPERIENCE NEEDED: NO

APPROPRIATE PLACEMENT FOR 1ST TIME DOG OWNER? YES

FREE OBEDIENCE TRAINING IS OFFERED WITH ALL DOG ADOPTIONS

Please note that we are often asked if dogs are "house trained". The dogs are in fact living in a kennel environment during their time with us. Even if they have previously lived in a home and been trained - the stress of the change and the new home can sometimes cause regression and require some additional training. We feel that it's best for all adopters to be prepared for this possibility.

Visit our adoption page for details about our process, and to fill out an adoption application. All animals come spayed/neutered, UTD on vaccines, and microchipped. If the animals age or health prevents any of these from being completed prior to adoption a voucher is issued for the services to be performed. If you have any questions about the animal, or our adoption process, please email adopt@littleguild.org. The Little Guild is a 501c(3) federally recognized non-profit organization devoted to saving the lives of homeless pets.

animal.description:
Rhi is living in a foster home. Submit an application from our website and then make an appointment to meet her.

Rhi is not eligible for foster and will be a straight adoption.

Age: ~3 years
Weight: ~58lbs
Housebroken: Working on it! She needs to be on a strict schedule
Crate trained: Working on it! Takes 10-30 minutes to settle but overall doing well with her crate-training
Dog sociability: She is leash reactive towards other dogs (barks/lunges).
Cat sociability: Unknown
Kids: Unknown, but she can be mouthy (play bites) so older kids are best.
Ideal home: Rhi is looking for an active adopter that can commit to training! Rhi does best when she gets exercised both inside and outside of the home everyday. She would prefer a quiet neighborhood where she doesn't have to pass a bunch of other dogs. She currently lives with a male in her foster, but she does prefer slow intros with high value snacks for meeting men. She is not a match for a high-rise/elevator building.

Rhi is excited about LIFE and she hopes you are, too! This bundle of energy will keep you on on your toes and snuggle her way into your heart. She loves to play and be showered with attention and she'll be sure to give it back to you 10 fold. She's always ready for a game of tug and war, which she never loses but she won't rub it in! Rhi would love an adopter that will continue to work on training as she is eager to please and will benefit from learning some impulse control and how to direct her energy in positive ways. She does fantastic when given enrichment toys, bones, etc. and of course loves a good 3 or so walks per day. If you're looking for an active adventure buddy to get you out of the house this dark winter, look no further!

Rhi's adoption fee is 300. She is spayed, up to date on core vaccines, microchipped and heartworm negative.

***We are receiving a much higher than usual number of adoption applications. We ask that you please be patient and someone will be in touch via email within 72 hours. Please do not email us unless you have not received a response in 72 hours. Please only fill out one adoption application. ***

animal.description:
Henry is a confident and outgoing pup! This 1-year-old Boxer mix is an active boy who loves to spend time with people. Henry would love a home where he can run around and play with toys in his fenced in yard. The kennel environment has been a bit stressful for Henry, so he would really love to relax in a home! Once he walks away from his kennel space, he shows you the love bug that he truly is--leaning into you for scratches and love. Henry would need to be the only dog in his home, as wants to soak up all your love.  He also would like a home without cats. Henry wants to please and would enjoy doing training with his new family so he can be the best dog you ever had. This boy is going to be the perfect companion for a very lucky owner. 

A physical fence is required for adoption.

If you want to meet Henry, please email Rescue@LamanchaAnimalRescue.org.

animal.description:
Breed: German Shepherd mix
Sex: Spayed Female
DOB: ~11/17/2017
Weight: 65 lbs
Energy Level: Low-Medium
Personality Type: Affectionate, SUPER Sweet, Well-Mannered, Low-Key
History: Transferred from another shelter
Good With: Dogs, Kids 8+ years
Fence Requirements: Preferred, not required
Ideal Home: Single-level home looking for a household companion. Ground-level apartments ok.
Special Info: Vera has old injuries to her rear legs that do not require surgery but she will be undergoing physical therapy to help increase her range of motion. She gets along just fine and can anything other dogs can do! She is already housebroken and loves relaxing!

The information we are providing for this animal was developed based on observations and assessments in a shelter or foster environment. We do our best to provide information that will help determine if the dog might be a good fit for you. Please note that behaviors may change in a home environment. We also ask our applicants to assume that any animal they adopt from us will need to be potty trained and learn house manners, although this is not always the case. Our online animal bios are designed to provide as much information as possible and answer some anticipated questions. We do not have the resources to respond to emails with more specific questions.

We are receiving an unusually high number of applications per pet at this time! Please follow the rules below to ensure your application is reviewed; pay attention closely to these instructions because applications will NOT be processed if they are not followed. Please keep in mind that dog/cat availability is currently changing by the hour; you will receive an email if the animal you are interested in is no longer available. New dogs become available almost every day, so feel free to let us know if someone else interests you if your initial choice is already adopted! 

Fill out the application (DOG: https://www.iheartdogs.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/IHD-DOG-Application-9-10-18.pdf, CAT: https://www.iheartdogs.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/IHD-CAT-Application.pdf) completely. Every question must be answered, and it must be signed. If you are going to type your responses, open the application, save it, type your answers, and save it again. 

-Applicants must be 21+ years old and live within a 50-mile radius of our shelter at 22415 Groesbeck Hwy, Warren 48089.

-You must identify at least 1 dog/cat that you are interested in. If there are multiple dogs/cats, number them in order of priority. 

-Scan a copy of proof of home ownership (i.e. tax bill, deed, or mortgage payment - you can black out the account #, etc.) or animal clause/agreement of your rental agreement.

-Attach the application and home ownership proof/rental agreement animal clause to a new email and send it to bark@iheartdogs.org. The subject line must be formatted to read ""#1 choice of dog/cat, Your First and Last Name"". Example: Subject: Fido, Jane Doe
Once your application is received, it will be assigned to an Adoption Counselor who will follow-up with the applicant who is the best fit within a few days, or to discuss other dogs/cats. It could take up to a couple of weeks for you to receive a final disposition on your application so there is no need to check on the status.

-Introductions will be scheduled by appointment only, 45 minutes per appointment. The entire household, including current dogs, must be present for the appointment. The introductions will take place outside in our parking lot.

-We will continue to perform vet checks for current and prior pets in the household.

-Home visits will be in person for the yard and virtual for inside the home.

-Finalizing the adoption will also be scheduled by appointment.

While this process may seem cumbersome, it is interim during COVID-19, and it is designed to help us respond to the volume of emails we receive every day. Since we are receiving a high volume of applications, please be patient if a dog/cat is no longer available. 

Thank you for your understanding.

I am fully house trained but I am still working on crate training. I am looking for a home without cats or dogs! I am a queen when on a leash and could do well in an apartment! My adoption fee is $150 and includes my spay/neuter, vaccinations, wellness exam, heartworm test, and microchip! If you're interested in meeting/adopting me, please visit www.rescueonespringfield.com/our-adoption-process/adoption-application/ and fill out the form! We do adopt out of state with vet references and video home check. *Adopter is responsible for coming to get the dog and returning the dog if the adoption does not work out* 

Don't forget to LIKE us on Facebook!-www.facebook.com/rescueonespringfield

*Remember, dogs are pack animals. Because of this, Rescue One does not adopt to outdoor-only homes. Pets are family and are not disposable.  Please make sure that you are 100% committed to a pet before considering adding one to your home.

animal.description:
Meet Momma Millie. This sweet girl was surrendered with her pups and the dad after her family could no longer care for them. All have been adopted except this sweet momma. Sadly, she has spent her life outdoors without much interaction so she is a bit shy at first. She warms up quick and doesn’t offer up an ounce of aggression. Millie truly is the sweetest soul. She just needs a little patience to settle into a new environment. She adores the kids in her foster home and actually stands guard while they are playing outdoors and follows them all over the farm. She’s great with other animals. She’s laid back and very sweet. Millie does prefer to be outdoors and enjoy her property during the day. She is getting more used to the indoor life and starting to enjoy that more. She sleeps all night inside without a peep. She’s learning a leash but still needs some work. She doesn’t mind a kennel and rides well in the car. She is a yellow lab mix around 3 years old and 50 lbs. This girl is truly the perfect farm pup. She is loyal, watchful, easy going and is as sweet as they come. This girl deserves nothing but the best. If you can give that to her please fill out the app below. Millie is utd, hw tested and spayed. 

All dogs have a $150 adoption fee which includes vet check, age appropriate shots (atleast 2 sets for puppies), dewormer, heartworm test (if over 6 months), rabies (if atleast 16 weeks) and spay/neuter!

Puppies/Dogs that are not available for adoption due to vetting not being complete can be reserved with an approved application and a non refundable $50 deposit. This deposit is applied to your adoption fee and the remaining $100 is due at pick up.

Wags and Whiskers is an all-volunteer rescue. We also have full-time jobs and Families. We will try to answer all questions and applications in a timely manner. Please be patient and bear with us . Do not contact Parkway Animal Hospital as they are a vet clinic and can not answer questions on behalf of Wags and Whiskers. All questions and comments must go directly through the rescue. Thank you for your understanding.

HIGH ENERGY...VERY INTELLIGENT!!!UPDATE 12/19/2020:
Pica (pronounced Peeka) is a male @2-year-old Heeler (mix) who weighs @35 pounds. He tested NEGATIVE times 4 on his test for Heartworm, Lyme, Ehrlichia and Anaplasmosis and this is always great news. Pica begs attention from every person he sees. His idea of a perfect day would include lots of stuff to see, chasing balls, being petted, running, running, running and problem-solving games. In the right hands, he would do great as an agility dog. The right hands would be a person who understands the energy needs of working breeds like his and their desire to do a job, and what happens if they are left and become bored.
This boy is brilliant and can learn any task if you can translate what you want and provide a reasonable incentive. Pica adores activity of almost any kind, but he has an aversion to water, so swimming sports might be a no-go. And though he likes kids and gets very protective of them, he has been known to bite when something concerns him, so small kids or unattended kids are not a good idea. Pica may feel a need to intervene if someone interacts with the child he is focused on. When people hug, it upsets him and causes a barking frenzy. He needs a firm (not harsh) person to give him direction.
Pica has a high prey drive and has decided that cats are fair game as quarry, merely another varmint to rid the world of. And though he seems friendly enough towards other dogs at our facility, his surrenderer told us he was a bully with their other very submissive dog. We were also informed that if left alone and unconfined, Pica demonstrated mild separation anxiety by barking and chewing personal items left out.
Pica is playful as a puppy, takes treats gently from fingers, enjoys being petted, and has good house manners and was trained to stay off furniture.
This eager boy plaintively calls out in a typical Heeler squeal when folks pass his room as if saying, Come play with me. I promise it will be worth it.
Pica is currently living at the Nelson County Humane Society/SPCA Almost Home Pet Adoption Center near Lovingston, VA, and Lindsey at lindsey21581@gmail.com is the point of contact for him. If you are interested in him and have what he needs, please fill out an on-line application for him at www.nelsonspca.org and email Lindsey too. VOLUNTEERS and DONATIONS NEEDED. Visit our website for more info: http://nelsonspca.org

animal.description:
Reese is a 3.5 year old female shepherd mix. This beautiful brindle weighs around 65 lbs. Reese was adopted from us as a puppy and returned recently through no fault of her own. She has made amazing progress since coming back into our care. She’s incredibly sweet with people she’s comfortable with and very affectionate. Reese would do best with an experienced dog owner. To adopt Reese, apply at ITVrescue.org.

All of our animals are examined by a veterinarian, given age-appropriate vaccinations, dewormed, microchipped, spayed or neutered, heartworm tested and treated if necessary.

Please realize that many of our animals are kept in foster homes. Please complete an adoption application at http://itvrescue.org/adoption-application/ in order to meet with one of our animals. There is no obligation in completing the application, but it helps us find an animal that is most appropriate for your family.  The ITV Rescue Center is open Tuesdays 12-5; Wednesdays 12-7; Thursdays 12-5; Fridays 12-5 and Saturdays 10-5.  The Rescue Center is located at 1417 N. Stockwell Road.  You are welcome to come to our rescue center during open hours to see all of our great adoptable animals. Thank you for your interest in our animals!

NOTE: Visual breed identification in dogs is unreliable, so for most of the dogs we are only guessing at predominant breed or breed mix. We get to know each dog as an individual and will do our best to describe each of our dogs based on personality, not by breed label.

animal.description:
Meet the #CatsOfGettysburg... to donate toward the care of the large number of cats and kittens our volunteers care for everyday visit paypal.me/foreverloverescue - please note that while we work hard to keep our available cats up to date we also have many kittens that do not show up on these websites because they get come and go so fast! Apply to adopt at foreverloverescue.com and we will help you find the purr-fect kitty for your family!
Hera

Pitbull mix

Black

55lbs

Hera loves every person she meets. She loves to cuddle and is good with kids. Perfect family dog. Does well with dogs her size or bigger (but not small dogs). Unsure about how she does with cats. House-trained but can have accidents when she has a bladder infection. This has been an ongoing issue and her current family has been hit hard financially due to the pandemic this year. Can you help us find Hera a great home where she can receive the time and care she deserves. Apply to adopt online at https://foreverloverescue.com/dog-adoptionfoster-application/

All of the cats listed are located in or near Gettysburg, Pennsylvania unless otherwise noted. Adoption fees are $60 for adult cats and kittens over 6 months old, $100 for kittens (under 6 months) and $30 for senior cats (7 years+) to help cover vet bills for spay/neuter, basic vaccinations, testing, microchips and preventatives. No cat will be officially adopted without being spayed/neutered and rabies vaccinated (unless there are health risks in doing so). We highly recommend adopting kittens in pairs and we do discount for double adoptions here to encourage it. Visit many of our kitties at our Kitty Corner adoption center 39 Queen St in historic Gettysburg PA.

We will require an approved on-line application which is available on our website at

foreverloverescue.com/cat-application/

Please feel free to call 717-900-5525 with any questions, or reach us by email at friends@foreverloverescue.com. Be sure to check us out on Facebook at

https://www.facebook.com/ForeverLoveRescue/

and "LIKE" our page. SAVING ONE CAT MAY NOT CHANGE THE WORLD...BUT FOR THAT ONE CAT, THE WORLD CHANGES FOREVER! Please, Don't Shop, ADOPT A BEST FRIEND! <3

animal.description: If the qualifications for your next pet are big, goofy, and might actually be a cow, then we have just the one for you! Jax is a 3-year-old dog who is looking for someone he can love on.A bit shy at first, and curious of strangers, Jax warms up quickly to people. After first introductions, it doesnt take long for him to lean against you, hoping for a back scratch. And if he catches you sitting down, you best hope you have legs of steelthis big boy does not seem to understand just how large he is, as he will assume the role of a lap dog.Jax is a mixed bag when it comes to his breed. While he is officially listed at a pittie, his head looks more like a labs, and the curve of his tail is reminiscent of an akitas. Jax has white fur with black spots, and his habit of eating grass all the time really completes the picture of his resemblance to a cow.Jax is a moderate-energy pooch, as he likes to frolic three times around the Big Yard before laying on his tummy, all four legs sprawled out. If you have a rope toy, he can be tempted to have a bit more fun, and he will chase you all day if you have treats.Jax does have a history of resource guarding his food, and while he has not shown signs of aggression toward any of our staff, we would recommend that he go to a home without young children or other pets. Jax would really thrive with someone who can give him the attention he craves and would be game to spend time training him on some basic obedience skills.Are you udderly in love with Jax already? Then head to kenthumane.org to submit your application! Due to COVID-19 precautions, the Animal Care Shelter for Kent County is open by appointment only. Once your application is approved, we will set up an appointment with you!Animal meetings and adoptions by appointment only. Please go to kenthumane.org/adoption-applicationOnce approved we will call you to set up an appointment!
